  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Owen</b> is a male name in Westeros. It may refer to:\n</p>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Owen_(brother_of_Meribald)\" title=\"Owen (brother of Meribald)\">Owen</a>, deceased brother of Septon Meribald</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Owen_(knight)\" title=\"Owen (knight)\">Owen</a>, a knight from the Vale of Arryn</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Owen_the_Oaf\" title=\"Owen the Oaf\">Owen the Oaf</a>, a steward of the Night's Watch</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Owen_Bush\" title=\"Owen Bush\">Owen Bush</a>, a Kingsguard for King Maegor I Targaryen</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Owen_Costayne\" title=\"Owen Costayne\">Owen Costayne</a>, Lord of Three Towers during the Dance of the Dragons</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Owen_Fossoway\" title=\"Owen Fossoway\">Owen Fossoway</a>, Lord of Cider Hall during the Dance of the Dragons</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Owen_Inchfield\" title=\"Owen Inchfield\">Owen Inchfield</a>, a knight in Renly Baratheon's camp</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Owen_Merryweather\" title=\"Owen Merryweather\">Owen Merryweather</a>, Lord of Longtable and a Hand of the King to Aerys II Targaryen</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Owen_Norrey\" title=\"Owen Norrey\">Owen Norrey</a>, a northern mountain clansman</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Owen_Oakenshield\" title=\"Owen Oakenshield\">Owen Oakenshield</a>, a legendary son of Garth Greenhand</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Owen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: See also\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Owain_Bourney\" title=\"Owain Bourney\">Owain Bourney</a></li></ul>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260405014006\nCache expiry: 1209600